The paper discusses deep neural networks and their deployment on limited computational resources, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning): This sub-category is the most likely as the paper discusses a machine learning algorithm for compressing neural networks. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper mentions image recognition as one of the tasks where deep neural networks have been successful, which suggests that it could belong to this sub-category. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for predictive modeling tasks, which is a common application of artificial intelligence. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper focuses on neural networks, which suggests that it could belong to this sub-category. 

cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper discusses the deployment of neural networks on limited computational resources, which could involve distributed, parallel, or cluster computing.
